Why do scientists feel the need to write publication-quality documents?  After all, in
bygone days, getting a document to publication standard was the task of a professional
copy-editor.  The scientist's responsibility was getting the content right.

One answer to this question is the desire of all scientists to communicate the results of
their effort in the best possible light.  Such a desire we can all appreciate, but this is not
the right answer.  The overwhelming consideration for the scientist is the desire to
